defs.name: cursor
defs.docs:
A module to work with the terminal cursor
 # Cursor

defs.name: MoveTo
defs.docs: A command that moves the terminal cursor to the given position (column, row).

defs.name: MoveToNextLine
defs.docs:
A command that moves the terminal cursor up the given number of lines,
 and moves it to the first column.

defs.name: MoveToPreviousLine
defs.docs:
A command that moves the terminal cursor down the given number of lines,
 and moves it to the first column.

defs.name: MoveToColumn
defs.docs: A command that moves the terminal cursor to the given column on the current row.

defs.name: MoveUp
defs.docs: A command that moves the terminal cursor a given number of rows up.

defs.name: MoveRight
defs.docs: A command that moves the terminal cursor a given number of columns to the right.

defs.name: MoveDown
defs.docs: A command that moves the terminal cursor a given number of rows down.

defs.name: MoveLeft
defs.docs: A command that moves the terminal cursor a given number of columns to the left.

defs.name: SavePosition
defs.docs: A command that saves the current terminal cursor position.

defs.name: RestorePosition
defs.docs: A command that restores the saved terminal cursor position.

defs.name: Hide
defs.docs: A command that hides the terminal cursor.

defs.name: Show
defs.docs: A command that shows the terminal cursor.

defs.name: EnableBlinking
defs.docs: A command that enables blinking of the terminal cursor.

defs.name: DisableBlinking
defs.docs: A command that disables blinking of the terminal cursor.

defs.name: event
defs.docs:
A module to read events.
 # Event

defs.name: poll
defs.docs: Checks if there is an [`Event`](enum.Event.html) available.

defs.name: EnableMouseCapture
defs.docs: A command that enables mouse event capturing.

defs.name: DisableMouseCapture
defs.docs: A command that disables mouse event capturing.

defs.name: Key
defs.docs: A single key event with additional pressed modifiers.

defs.name: Mouse
defs.docs: A singe mouse event with additional pressed modifiers.

defs.name: Resize
defs.docs: An resize event with new dimensions after resize (columns, rows).

defs.name: Drag
defs.docs: Moved mouse pointer while pressing a mouse button.

defs.name: ScrollDown
defs.docs: Scrolled mouse wheel downwards (towards the user).

defs.name: ScrollUp
defs.docs: Scrolled mouse wheel upwards (away from the user).

defs.name: KeyCode
defs.value: KeyCode::{Backspace, Enter, Left, Right, Up, Down, Home, End, PageUp, PageDown, Tab, BackTab, Delete, Insert, F, Char, Null, Esc}

defs.name: style
defs.docs:
A module to apply attributes and colors on your text.
 # Style

defs.name: ContentStyle
defs.docs: The style that can be put on content.

defs.name: apply
defs.docs: Creates a `StyledContent` by applying the style to the given `val`.

defs.name: SlowBlink
defs.docs: Makes the text blinking (< 150 per minute).

defs.name: RapidBlink
defs.docs: Makes the text blinking (>= 150 per minute).

defs.name: Hidden
defs.docs: Hides the text (also known as Conceal).

defs.name: NormalIntensity
defs.docs: Switches the text back to normal intensity (no bold, italic).

defs.name: NoBlink
defs.docs: Turns off the text blinking (`SlowBlink` or `RapidBlink`).

defs.name: OverLined
defs.docs: Draws a line at the top of the text.

defs.name: Attribute
defs.value: Attribute::{Reset, Bold, Dim, Italic, Underlined, SlowBlink, RapidBlink, Reverse, Hidden, CrossedOut, Fraktur, NoBold, NormalIntensity, NoItalic, NoUnderline, NoBlink, NoReverse, NoHidden, NotCrossedOut, Framed, Encircled, OverLined, NotFramedOrEncircled, NotOverLined, __Nonexhaustive}

defs.name: Rgb
defs.docs: An RGB color. See [RGB color model](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RGB_color_model) for more info.

defs.name: AnsiValue
defs.docs: An ANSI color. See [256 colors - cheat sheet](https://jonasjacek.github.io/colors/) for more info.

defs.name: Color
defs.value: Color::{Reset, Black, DarkGrey, Red, DarkRed, Green, DarkGreen, Yellow, DarkYellow, Blue, DarkBlue, Magenta, DarkMagenta, Cyan, DarkCyan, White, Grey, Rgb, AnsiValue}

defs.name: StyledContent
defs.docs: The style with the content to be styled.

defs.name: Colorize
defs.docs: Provides a set of methods to set the colors.

defs.name: Styler
defs.docs: Provides a set of methods to set the text attributes.

defs.name: SetForegroundColor
defs.docs: A command that sets the the foreground color.

defs.name: SetBackgroundColor
defs.docs: A command that sets the the background color.

defs.name: SetAttribute
defs.docs: A command that sets an attribute.

defs.name: PrintStyledContent
defs.docs: A command that prints styled content.

defs.name: ResetColor
defs.docs: A command that resets the colors back to default.

defs.name: Print
defs.docs: A command that prints the given displayable type.

defs.name: terminal
defs.docs:
A module to work with the terminal.
 # Terminal

defs.name: EnterAlternateScreen
defs.docs: A command that switches to alternate screen.

defs.name: LeaveAlternateScreen
defs.docs: A command that switches back to the main screen.

defs.name: FromCursorDown
defs.docs: All cells from the cursor position downwards.

defs.name: FromCursorUp
defs.docs: All cells from the cursor position upwards.

defs.name: CurrentLine
defs.docs: All cells at the cursor row.

defs.name: UntilNewLine
defs.docs: All cells from the cursor position until the new line.

defs.name: ClearType
defs.docs: Different ways to clear the terminal buffer.

defs.name: ScrollUp
defs.docs: A command that scrolls the terminal screen a given number of rows up.

defs.name: ScrollDown
defs.docs: A command that scrolls the terminal screen a given number of rows down.

defs.name: Clear
defs.docs: A command that clears the terminal screen buffer.

defs.name: SetSize
defs.docs: A command that sets the terminal size `(columns, rows)`.

defs.name: Command
defs.docs: An interface for a command that performs an action on the terminal.

defs.name: ansi_code
defs.docs:
Returns an ANSI code representation of this command.
 An ANSI code can manipulate the terminal by writing it to the terminal buffer.
 However, only Windows 10 and UNIX systems support this.

defs.name: QueueableCommand
defs.docs: An interface for commands that can be queued for further execution.

defs.name: queue
defs.value: fn (&mut self, command: impl Command<AnsiType = T>) -> Result<&mut Self>
defs.docs: Queues the given command for further execution.

defs.name: ExecutableCommand
defs.docs: An interface for commands that are directly executed.

defs.name: execute
defs.value: fn (&mut self, command: impl Command<AnsiType = T>) -> Result<&mut Self>

defs.name: ErrorKind
defs.docs: Wrapper for all errors that can occur in `crossterm`.
